Hello,

For your security, we have suspended your email account due to suspicious activity.  You will be unable to access, send or receive email during this time.
 
To restore your email account, you will need to chat with our Email Support Team.  Our support team will inform you of best practices to ensure you stay protected while using CenturyLink Email and assist you in regaining access to your account.
 
To chat with an agent, please click the blue chat button in the lower right-hand corner of the Help Center (9:00-6:00 CT, Monday-Friday).

This could have occurred many ways, most common causes include:
  • A weak password.
  • Malware, Key Loggers, Viruses from Phishing emails.
  • You may have accessed your email through an unsecured network or public computer.
  • Using repeated credentials (An email and password also used with other Internet services: Amazon, Facebook, etc.)"
Thank you,

CenturyLink Email Support

If you have any more problems or questions, please don’t hesitate to let us know.

Hello,

We’re sorry that you’ve experienced the problem you described below and apologize for the inconvenience it’s caused. It looks like you’re going to have to execute a few steps to resolve this problem. This guide should be able to walk you through the entire process:

Troubleshoot errors when connecting an inbox with IMAP
When you connect your CenturyLink inbox via IMAP, you might receive an error during the connection process or in your email integration settings. To better understand why the error occurred, review the steps that take place in order to successfully connect your inbox via IMAP.

IMAP Authentication Troubleshooting:
Please attempt to authenticate at webmail.centurylink.net on a PC/Mac using a browser.
If such authentication is successful, the password is correct, and no password reset is required.
a. It is recommended to retype the password in the mobile device and try again.
b. If that second attempt fails, then additional attempts are recommended.
c. A password reset is not necessary.

If that authentication fails after multiple attempts and you have checked your Server Settings, then a password reset is needed. To reset your password, please contact CenturyLink Live Chat Support agent.

To chat with an agent, please click the blue chat button in the lower right-hand corner of the Help Center (9:00-6:00 CT, Monday-Friday).

If you have any more problems, please don’t hesitate to let us know.

Have a great day!

CenturyLink Email Support

Hello %filltext:name=Customer First Name:width=20:default=First Name%,
 
Thank you for reaching out to us regarding your password reset request. We understand that forgetting your password can be frustrating and we are here to assist you.
 
Unfortunately, we are unable to process password reset requests through email or ticketing systems, as it is a security measure to protect your email account. However, we can assist you with resetting your password through our live chat service. To chat with a live agent, please click the blue Chat button in the bottom right corner of the Help Center (8:00-5:00 ET, Monday-Friday).
 
Please note that for security reasons, we will need to verify your identity before resetting your password. Therefore, please have your account information ready when you contact our live chat agent.
 
We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause, and we appreciate your understanding. If you have any other issues or concerns, please don't hesitate to reach out to us.
 
Have a great day!
 
CenturyLink Email Support

Hello,

Thank you for reaching out to support department.

The account in question was temporary suspended due to suspicious SPAM sending activity.

To unblock the account, please login to your account using new webmail https://webmail.centurylink.net/app/, update the password and Recovery Options from account Settings and run virus scan on your PC. Once done, please re-log in to the account to take effect.

Please use credentials below to access the account via new webmail using desktop / laptop browser version:

- sign in page: https://webmail.centurylink.net/app/
- email: [email address]
- password: [your current password]

You can find the instructions on how to update password and Recovery Options from account Settings in this Online Help Center article: https://centurylinkwebmail.s.center/hc/en-us/articles/9653627726739-How-to-change-your-CenturyLink-email-password

Kind regards,
CenturyLink Support department.

Hello %filltext:name=Customer Name:width=20:default=(First Name)%,

Thank you for reaching out to support department. We checked the account and found no blockings applied. If you are not receiving messages from specific senders, please login to your account in webmail https://webmail.centurylink.net/app/ using the desktop / laptop browser and check the following:

- Check Spam folders in webmail https://webmail.centurylink.net/app/ from desktop or laptop browser;
- If the messages found in Spam folder, you can

a) Mark them as NOT spam,
b) Move to Inbox;
c) Manually add the sender(s) email address to the Safe List: https://centurylinkwebmail.s.center/hc/en-us/articles/8586851686163-Create-Safe-List
This will update the spam filters logic and further mail from that specific sender will go to Inbox.

- Check the Rules in Settings to make sure that mail is not re-directed to any custom folder:
https://centurylinkwebmail.s.center/hc/en-us/articles/8586664532371-Create-Email-Rules-Filters-- check the Blocked Sender list in 

- Settings to make sure that the messages from specific sender are not getting blocked: https://centurylinkwebmail.s.center/hc/en-us/articles/8586751260691-Block-or-Unblock-a-Sender

- Check Junk Mail in Settings to make sure that the setting is not set to "Exclusive Delivery": https://centurylinkwebmail.s.center/hc/en-us/articles/8586793765523-Junk-Mail

%snippet:,,ending%
to sign in via https://webmail.centurylink.net/app/?
